```ts
export const x = 2;

export const y = () => 2

export function z() { return 2 }
```

![screen shot 2017-02-22 at 12 42 49 am](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/212305/23203584/fa7fde88-f897-11e6-9114-1ed3bf9de3d1.png)

The bug seems to be that TS only returns the `() => 2` span as the symbol location for `y`

```
 {
            "text": "x",
            "kind": "const",
            "kindModifiers": "export",
            "spans": [
                {
                    "start": {
                        "line": 1,
                        "offset": 14
                    },
                    "end": {
                        "line": 1,
                        "offset": 19
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "y",
            "kind": "function",
            "kindModifiers": "export",
            "spans": [
                {
                    "start": {
                        "line": 3,
                        "offset": 18
                    },
                    "end": {
                        "line": 3,
                        "offset": 25
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
```

Both `x` and `y` should have the same offset, but `x` has an offset of 14 which correctly marks the start of the `x = 2` expression, while `y` has an offset of `18` which starts at `() => 2`

This causes the references request to fail for `y`:

```
[Trace - 12:42:49 AM] Sending request: references (2824). Response expected: yes. Current queue length: 1
Arguments: {
    "file": "untitled:Untitled-1",
    "line": 3,
    "offset": 18
}
[Trace - 12:42:49 AM] Response received: references (2824). Request took 79 ms. Success: false . Message: No content available.
```

In a scss file:

```scss
body {
    font-feature-settings: "kern" 1;
    font-kerning: normal;
}
```

Both `font-feature-settings` and `font-kerning` are split into two sections instead of being a single property:

